00:15:36.110 --> 00:15:40.060
If you excite something
that resonates,

00:15:40.060 --> 00:15:44.520
then it's going to resonate 90
degrees out of phase, isn't it?

00:15:44.520 --> 00:15:51.630
So if you've got a point source
and you excite it with a wave,

00:15:51.630 --> 00:15:56.730
then the scattered wave is going
to be 90 degrees out of phase

00:15:56.730 --> 00:16:00.780
with the driving force, just
because it's like a resonance.

00:16:00.780 --> 00:16:04.860
And I guess that's also
true in the Huygens' thing

00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:08.200
that we come on in
the next lecture.

00:16:08.200 --> 00:16:08.700
But yeah.

