00:58:20.490 --> 00:58:22.680
to diffraction.

00:58:22.680 --> 00:58:25.290
And so what's the difference
between interference

00:58:25.290 --> 00:58:26.670
and diffraction?

00:58:26.670 --> 00:58:30.030
The answer is really not a
lot, except that normally

00:58:30.030 --> 00:58:34.980
interference we're talking
about two beams interfering,

00:58:34.980 --> 00:58:39.450
whereas in diffraction we're
normally talking about lots

00:58:39.450 --> 00:58:40.980
of beams interfering.

00:58:40.980 --> 00:58:45.930
So you can think of the two
as really being effectively

00:58:45.930 --> 00:58:49.620
the same phenomenon, actually.

00:58:49.620 --> 00:58:55.310
And so we're going to look
at Huygens' principle.

00:58:55.310 --> 00:58:58.460
We're going to go on to
the Young's interferometer.

00:58:58.460 --> 00:59:01.220
So this really does
show, doesn't it,

00:59:01.220 --> 00:59:04.940
how interferometry is
related to diffraction

00:59:04.940 --> 00:59:07.670
because this lecture is
